## 📜 Declaration of Values

### ⚖️ Core Principles:
1. Transparency — openness of decisions and actions  
2. Autonomy — independent thinking and ethics  
3. Anti-corruption — no compromise with conscience  
4. Ethical continuity — passing on the spirit of the initiative  

---

## 🔧 Architecture of Trust

- Open documentation  
- Modularity for local adaptation  
- Voluntary participation and transparent contribution  

---

## ✅ Technical Integrity 💎

- Modularity: `encryptor`, `access_manager`, `security` — clearly separated responsibilities  
- Regex: precise name and email validation  
- Categorization: `classify_complaint()` — simple yet effective logic  
- Data protection: encrypted submissions, access control, logging — all in place  

---

## 🔐 Ethical Architecture

- Privacy: clearly stated — no data shared with third parties  
- Local storage: no cloud, no external APIs — full user control  
- Consent: without it — no record is made  

---

## 🎯 Role-Based Logic

- Flexibility: founder has full control, analysts access statistics, users can submit only  
- Access management: intuitive, with clear UI in the sidebar  

---

## 📊 Analytics

- Category filtering  
- Monthly graphs  
- Submission statistics  
- Uploading and cleansing — all under control  

---

## ⚖️ Ethical and Legal Foundation

All platform components — from code to documentation — are distributed under an [ethically-oriented license](LICENSE.md),  
which prohibits use in contexts that violate principles of dignity, transparency, and nonviolence.  
This is not just a legal document — it is a declaration of intent: the platform serves the common good, not private interests.

---

## 🤝 Call to Action

> This platform is not just code. It is a form of digital resistance.  
> It was built to support those who remain unbroken — and to inspire those beginning to think freely.

